  <description type="morphology">Plants 1–2.5(–3) cm. Leaves of stipe and basal fronds in 8 rows, to 0.9 mm; dorsal frond leaves present on basal portion of stipe; distal stipe leaves often asymmetric, 1.2–1.7(–2) mm, margins entire to evenly serrate in distal 1/4–1/2; all leaves ovate to very short-acuminate; costa short or to 4/5 leaf length. Perichaetia with paraphyses absent. Seta 1–1.5(–2.5) cm, smooth or weakly papillose distally. Capsule 1–1.5 mm; operculum rostrate, 1.2–1.5 mm.</description>
